      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and roughly shred</p><p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>finely, then combine the <strong>sliced red chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> [2 tsp]<strong> </span>sugar </strong>and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>rice vinegar</strong> (save the rest for later!) and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>quick-pickled chilli</strong></p>",
